Key Match Events: Ireland made 157 and bowled superbly to restrict England to 105 for five when rain stopped play and Ireland took victory under the DLS method.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Eleven years on from their 50-over World Cup upset win over the same opponents at Bangalore, Ireland have blown this Super 12s group wide open with England needing to win their three remaining fixtures to finish in the top two, starting against arch rivals Australia at the same venue on Friday evening.
Others: Ireland got off to a flyer on Wednesday with Chris Woakes leaking 41 from his three overs as they reached 103 for one after 11.5 overs although several of their batters were unsettled by Mark Wood, who took three for 34, while Liam Livingstone also claimed his first three-wicket haul in an England shirt.
